Extend the subnet_config module to accept an optional public_test_key_word flag for each subnet.
Use locals to split subnets into public and private groups based on the flag.
Deploy an Internet Gateway only if at least one subnet is marked public.
Create a public route table only when public subnets exist.
Add a default route (0.0.0.0/0) in the public route table pointing to the Internet Gateway.
Associate all public subnets with the public route table.
Output both public and private subnet maps for visibility (public_subnet_display, private_subnet_display).
Ensure VPC details and subnet definitions are passed cleanly into the module without altering existing structure.
Keep resource naming consistent (own_vpc, own_gw, pub_rtb, public_asso) for clarity.
Validate CIDR blocks in variable.tf to prevent misconfiguration.
Use conditional count logic (length(local.public_subnet_check) > 0 ? 1 : 0) to avoid deploying unnecessary resources.
Maintain modularity by keeping all subnet logic inside serviceroad and exposing outputs in own_module.tf.
Ensure tags are applied consistently across VPC, subnets, and gateway for easier identification.
Document the purpose of each resource in comments for future maintainers.
Keep provider versions pinned (aws >= 6.42.0, random 3.8.1) for stability.

This repository contains a modular Terraform configuration designed to spin up a custom AWS Virtual Private Cloud (VPC) along with dynamic subnet provisioning, routing tables, and internet gateway attachments.

