## Root Configuration

### `terra.tf`

This file configures the basic Terraform environment requirements and details the cloud provider region.

```hcl
terraform {
  required_providers {
    # Telling Terraform which providers to download and use
    aws = {
      source  = "hashicorp/aws"
      version = ">= 6.42.0"
    }

    random = {
      source  = "hashicorp/random"
      version = "3.8.1"
    }
  }
}

# Configuring the AWS region
provider "aws" {
  region = "ap-south-1"
  alias  = "ubuntu_IND"
}

```

### `own_terra_network_module.tf`

This block calls our internal network module (`serviceroad`) and feeds it the explicit IP configurations and map structures for generating the network layout.

```hcl
module "highway_plus_vpc" {
  source = "./serviceroad" # Pointing to the folder where our resource code lives

  # Passing the VPC IP block and tags down to the module
  highway_vpc_details = {
    vpc_cidr_highway = "10.0.0.0/16"
    tags = {
      Name = "Highway_service_vpc"
    }
  }

  # Defining the subnets I want created. The module will loop through these.
  all_sub_details = {
    subnet_1 = {
      cidr_block_highway = "10.0.1.0/24"
    }
    subnet_2 = {
      cidr_block_highway = "10.0.2.0/24"
      #public_test_key_word = true #Enabling This key word to true would result into making  a subnet as public or private
    }
  }
}

```

### `own_module.tf`

Exposes outputs derived directly from the loaded `highway_plus_vpc` infrastructure module execution.

```hcl
output "module_public_subnet_display_doll" {
  value = module.highway_plus_vpc.public_subnet_display
}

output "module_private_subnet_display" {
  value = module.highway_plus_vpc.private_subnet_display
}

```

